        122
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Describes Virtual Machines, Docker and Linux ontainers, and their usage in groups of each in Azure, including the benefits of each and scenarios in which each approach works very well.",
      "pos": [
        142,
        326
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Virtual Machines and Containers in Azure",
      "pos": [
        787,
        827
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure offers you great cloud solutions, built on virtual machines&amp;mdash;based on the emulation of physical computer hardware&amp;mdash;to enable agile movement of software deployments and dramatically better resource consolidation than physical hardware.",
      "pos": [
        829,
        1079
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the past few years, largely thanks to  the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Docker<ept id=\"p1\">](https://www.docker.com)</ept> approach to containers and the docker ecosystem, Linux container technology has dramatically expanded the ways you can develop and manage distributed software.",
      "pos": [
        1080,
        1318
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Application code in a container is isolated from the host Azure VM as well as other containers on the same VM, which gives you more development and deployment agility at the application level&amp;mdash;in addition to the agility that Azure VMs already give you.",
      "pos": [
        1319,
        1576
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "But that's old news.",
      "pos": [
        1580,
        1600
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>new<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> news is that Azure offers you even more Docker goodness:",
      "pos": [
        1603,
        1669
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1673,
        1979
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Many<ept id=\"p1\">](virtual-machines-docker-with-xplat-cli.md)</ept> <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>different<ept id=\"p2\">](virtual-machines-docker-with-portal.md)</ept> <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>ways<ept id=\"p3\">](virtual-machines-docker-ubuntu-quickstart.md)</ept> to <bpt id=\"p4\">[</bpt>create Docker hosts<ept id=\"p4\">](https://github.com/Azure/azure-quickstart-templates/tree/master/docker-simple-on-ubuntu)</ept> for containers to suit your situation"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1982,
        2172
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Resource Manager<ept id=\"p1\">](resource-group-overview.md)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>resource group templates<ept id=\"p2\">](resource-group-authoring-templates.md)</ept> to simplify deploying and updating complex distributed applications"
    },
    {
      "content": "integration with a large array of both proprietary and open-source configuration management tools",
      "pos": [
        2175,
        2272
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2274,
        2627
      ],
      "content": "And because you can programmatically create VMs and Linux containers on Azure, you can also use VM and container <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>orchestration<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> tools to create groups of Virtual Machines (VMs) and to deploy applications inside both Linux containers and soon <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Windows Server Containers<ept id=\"p2\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/virtualization/windowscontainers/about/about_overview)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "This article not only discusses these concepts at a high level, it also contains tons of links to more information, tutorials, and products related to container and cluster usage on Azure.",
      "pos": [
        2630,
        2818
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you know all this, and just want the links, they're <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>right here<ept id=\"p1\">](#tools-for-working-with-containers)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2819,
        2923
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The difference between virtual machines and containers",
      "pos": [
        2928,
        2982
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Virtual machines run inside an isolated hardware virtualization environment provided by a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>hypervisor<ept id=\"p1\">](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypervisor)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2984,
        3128
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In Azure, the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Virtual Machines<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/services/virtual-machines/)</ept> service handles all that for you: You just create Virtual Machines by choosing the operating system and configuring it to run the way you want&amp;mdash;or by uploading your own custom VM image.",
      "pos": [
        3129,
        3407
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Virtual Machines are a time-tested, \"battle-hardened\" technology, and there are many tools available to manage operating systems and to configure the applications you install and run.",
      "pos": [
        3408,
        3591
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Anything running in a virtual machine is hidden from the host operating system and, from the point of view of an application or user running inside a virtual machine, the virtual machine appears to be an autonomous physical computer.",
      "pos": [
        3592,
        3825
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Linux containers<ept id=\"p1\">](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LXC)</ept>&amp;mdash;which includes those created and hosted using docker tools, and there are other approaches&amp;mdash;do not require or use a hypervisor to provide isolation.",
      "pos": [
        3827,
        4039
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Instead, the container host uses the process and file system isolation features of the Linux kernel to expose to the container (and its application) only certain kernel features and its own isolated file system (at a minimum).",
      "pos": [
        4040,
        4266
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "From the point of view of an application running inside a container, the container appears to be a unique operating system instance.",
      "pos": [
        4267,
        4399
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A contained application cannot see processes or any other resources outside of its container.",
      "pos": [
        4400,
        4493
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Because in this isolation and execution model the kernel of the Docker host computer is shared, and because the disk requirements of the container now do not include an entire operating system, both the start-up time of the container and the required disk storage overhead are much, much smaller.",
      "pos": [
        4496,
        4792
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It's pretty cool.",
      "pos": [
        4795,
        4812
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Server Containers<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/virtualization/windowscontainers/about/about_overview)</ept> provide the same advantages as Linux containers for applications that run on Windows.",
      "pos": [
        4814,
        5009
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Windows Server Containers support the docker image format and the docker API.",
      "pos": [
        5010,
        5087
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "As a result, an application using Windows Server Containers can be developed, published, retrieved, and deployed using similar commands to those on Mac and Linux.",
      "pos": [
        5088,
        5250
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "That's in addition to having <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>new docker support in Microsoft Visual Studio<ept id=\"p1\">](https://visualstudiogallery.msdn.microsoft.com/6f638067-027d-4817-bcc7-aa94163338f0)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        5251,
        5413
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The larger <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>container ecosystem<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/virtualization/windowscontainers/about/container_ecosystem)</ept> will give everyone tools to do the work they need to do with containers.",
      "pos": [
        5414,
        5606
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "That's pretty cool, too.",
      "pos": [
        5608,
        5632
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Is this too good to be true?",
      "pos": [
        5638,
        5666
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Well, yes&amp;mdash;and no.",
      "pos": [
        5668,
        5691
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Containers, like any other technology, do not magically wipe away all the hard work required by distributed applications.",
      "pos": [
        5692,
        5813
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Yet, at the same time containers do really change:",
      "pos": [
        5814,
        5864
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "how fast application code can be developed and shared widely",
      "pos": [
        5868,
        5928
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "how fast and with what confidence it can be tested",
      "pos": [
        5931,
        5981
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "how fast and with what confidence it can be deployed",
      "pos": [
        5984,
        6036
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "That said, remember containers execute on a container host&amp;mdash;an operating system, and in Azure that means an Azure Virtual Machine.",
      "pos": [
        6038,
        6173
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Even if you already love the idea of containers, you're still going to need a VM infrastructure hosting the containers, but the benefits are that containers do not care on which VM they are running (although whether the container wants a Linux or Windows execution environment will be important, for example).",
      "pos": [
        6174,
        6483
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What are containers good for?",
      "pos": [
        6489,
        6518
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6520,
        6926
      ],
      "content": "They're great for many things, but they encourage&amp;mdash;as do <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Cloud Services<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/services/cloud-services/)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Azure Service Fabric<ept id=\"p2\">](service-fabric-overview.md)</ept>&amp;mdash;the creation of single-service, <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p3\">microservice]</ept>-oriented distributed applications, in which application design is based on more small, composable parts rather than on larger, more strongly coupled components."
    },
    {
      "content": "This is especially true in public cloud environments like Azure, in which you rent VMs when and where you want them.",
      "pos": [
        6929,
        7045
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Not only do you get isolation and rapid deployment and orchestration tools, but you can make more efficient application infrastructure decisions.",
      "pos": [
        7046,
        7191
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, you might currently have a deployment consisting of 9 Azure VMs of a large size for a highly-available, distributed application.",
      "pos": [
        7194,
        7335
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the components of this application can be deployed in containers, you might be able to use only 4 VMs and deploy your application components inside 20 containers for redundancy and load balancing.",
      "pos": [
        7336,
        7535
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is just an example, of course, but if you can do this in your scenario, you can adjust to usage spikes with more containers rather than more Azure VMs, and use the remaining overall CPU load much more efficiently than before.",
      "pos": [
        7538,
        7768
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In addition, there are many scenarios that do not lend themselves to a microservices approach; you will know best whether microservices and containers will help you.",
      "pos": [
        7770,
        7935
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Container benefits for developers",
      "pos": [
        7942,
        7975
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In general, it's easy to see that container technology is a step forward, but there are more specific benefits as well.",
      "pos": [
        7977,
        8096
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Let's take the example of Docker containers.",
      "pos": [
        8097,
        8141
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This topic will not dive deeply into Docker right now (read <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>What is Docker?<ept id=\"p1\">](https://www.docker.com/whatisdocker/)</ept>",
      "pos": [
        8142,
        8257
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "for that story, or <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>wikipedia<ept id=\"p1\">](http://wikipedia.org/wiki/Docker_%28software%29)</ept>), but Docker and its ecosystem offer tremendous benefits to both developers and IT professionals.",
      "pos": [
        8258,
        8435
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Developers take to Docker containers quickly, because above all it makes using Linux containers easy:",
      "pos": [
        8437,
        8538
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "They can use simple, incremental commands to create a fixed image that is easy to deploy and can automate building those images using a dockerfile",
      "pos": [
        8542,
        8688
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8691,
        8932
      ],
      "content": "They can share those images easily using simple, <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>git<ept id=\"p1\">](https://git-scm.com/)</ept>-style push and pull commands to <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>public<ept id=\"p2\">](https://registry.hub.docker.com/)</ept> or <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>private docker registries<ept id=\"p3\">](virtual-machines-docker-registry-on-azure-blob-storage.md)</ept>"
    },
    {
      "content": "They can think of isolated application components instead of computers",
      "pos": [
        8936,
        9006
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "They can use a large number of tools that understand docker containers and different base images",
      "pos": [
        9009,
        9105
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Container benefits for operations and IT professionals",
      "pos": [
        9111,
        9165
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "IT and operations professionals also benefit from the combination of containers and virtual machines.",
      "pos": [
        9167,
        9268
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "contained services are isolated from VM host execution environment",
      "pos": [
        9273,
        9339
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "contained code is verifiably identical",
      "pos": [
        9342,
        9380
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "contained services can be started, stopped, and moved quickly between development, test, and production environments",
      "pos": [
        9383,
        9499
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Features like these&amp;mdash;and there are more&amp;mdash;excite established businesses, where professional information technology organizations have the job of fitting resources&amp;mdash;including pure processing power&amp;mdash;to the tasks required to not only stay in business, but increase customer satisfaction and reach.",
      "pos": [
        9501,
        9814
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Small businesses, ISVs, and startups have exactly the same requirement, but they might describe it differently.",
      "pos": [
        9815,
        9926
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What are virtual machines good for?",
      "pos": [
        9932,
        9967
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Virtual machines provide the backbone of cloud computing, and that doesn't change.",
      "pos": [
        9969,
        10051
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If virtual machines start more slowly, have a larger disk footprint, and do not map directly to a microservices architecture, they do have very important benefits:",
      "pos": [
        10052,
        10215
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By default, they have much more robust default security protections for host computer",
      "pos": [
        10221,
        10306
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "They support any major OS and application configurations",
      "pos": [
        10310,
        10366
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "They have longstanding tool ecosystems for command and control",
      "pos": [
        10370,
        10432
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "They provide the execution environment to host containers",
      "pos": [
        10436,
        10493
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The last item is important, because a contained application still requires a specific operating system and CPU type, depending upon the calls the application will make.",
      "pos": [
        10495,
        10663
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It's important to remember that you install containers on VMs because they contain the applications you want to deploy; containers are not replacements for VMs or operating systems.",
      "pos": [
        10664,
        10845
      ]
    },
    {
