    {
      "content": "Deployment and management of entire groups of Azure VMs and containers",
      "pos": [
        13750,
        13820
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are several popular systems that can deploy entire groups of VMs and install Docker (or other Linux container host systems) on them as an automatable group.",
      "pos": [
        13822,
        13984
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For direct links, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>containers and tools<ept id=\"p1\">](#containers-and-vm-technologies)</ept> section, below.",
      "pos": [
        13985,
        14082
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are several systems that do this to a greater or lesser extent, and this list is not exhaustive.",
      "pos": [
        14083,
        14185
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Depending upon your skill set and scenarios, they may or may not be useful.",
      "pos": [
        14186,
        14261
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Docker has its own set of VM-creation tools (<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>docker-machine<ept id=\"p1\">](virtual-machines-docker-machine.md)</ept>) and a load-balancing, docker-container cluster management tool (<bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>swarm<ept id=\"p2\">](virtual-machines-docker-swarm.md)</ept>).",
